Innings break Sri Lanka are all out for 144 after winning the toss and electing to bat. Australia's bowlers were simply too good. Jhye Richardson was outstanding on debut and Pat Cummins finished with four wickets after getting the first of the day. Niroshan Dickwella played an excellent innings in the circumstances to lift the total up to 144. How will the new Australian opening pair of Harris and Burns fare under lights? We will find out shortly.
